sql:
SELECT AVG(CAST(success_rate AS REAL)) AS average_success_rate
FROM test_results
WHERE environment = 'integration';

SELECT AVG(CAST(success_rate AS REAL)) AS average_success_rate
FROM test_results
WHERE environment = 'staging';

external_knowledge:
- A 'test class' is a group of related tests; 
- A 'notification' refers to an alert or message sent when a test result is generated, indicating that the test has finished running;
- 'More than 10 tests run' means a test class has executed more than 10 individual test cases;
- 'At least one test failure' means a test class has at least one test case that did not pass;
- 'At least one notification' means a test class has triggered at least one notification when its test results were generated.

